cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on modeling pairs of sentences. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel attention-based convolutional neural network (CNN) architecture, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses tasks such as answer selection (AS), paraphrase identification (PI), and textual entailment (TE), which are related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
